  "texts": [
    "[AL15, Lot10]).Example 3.10.",
    "Let (B 2, g B) be a genus 2 surface with Ric(g B) = -1 2 g B.",
    "For N = R 2, we have G = det -1 (±1).",
    "Let ρ: π 1 (B) → G be the representation defined on a generating set {a 1, b 1, a 2, b 2 } of π 1 (B) byρ(a 1) = 0 1 1 0, ρ(a 1) = ρ(b 1) = ρ(b 2) = 1 0 0 1.",
    "Since ρ(π 1 (B)) ≤ O(2), the constant map h: B → det -1 (±1)/ O(2), h b = h is ρ-equivariant and totally geodesic."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}